          <center><img src="http://www.dancepro.co.jp/action-machine/phot/ninja-biglift.gif" width="390"><br />don't gay ninjas have rights too?</center> If they were all wearing yellow, blue, and green they'd all look like washed up Mortal Kombat extras.<br /><br />When I was a wee lad, about the size of your thumb actually, I wasn't really into ninjas. I was more into robot stuff-- always had a fascination with robots. Transformers were cool to me and Power rangers were on the top of this list because of the giant robots that came together as one...that was cool. But you know what was REALLY cool to me? a combination of both machine and ninja...<br /><center><h1>SUPERHUMAN SAMAURI CYBER-SQUAD</h1><img src="http://www.figurerealm.com/ItemPics/4485.jpg"><br />wow, that is a mouthful.</center> What better way to fight viruses than to digitize yourself with one of your musical instruments and go online to fight the virus with your bare hands? That and Robocop were really good. In fact Mrs. Robinson's little brother tried to watch Robocop to fall asleep to the other night and just couldn't. Now thats a properly-executed flick. If you simply can't stop watching it even though it was made 20 years ago...its a damn good flick.<br />
